<HEADLINE> Jordanian PM Leaves for UAE </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Jordanian Prime Minister Abdul
Salam Majali left here this afternoon for Abu Dhabi on a 3-day
official visit, Radio Jordan reported.
</P>
<P>
Majali will hold talks with United Arab Emirates' (UAE)
officials on the prospects of promoting bilateral relations in all
fields as well as Arab and regional issues of mutual concern, the
official radio reported.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister is accompanied by Minister of Transport
and Telecommunications Bassam Saket and Minister of State for
Information Affairs Samir Mutawe.
</P>
<P>
UAE is one of the Arab countries that severed ties with Jordan
during the Gulf War (1990-1991) but recently has approached the
kingdom. 
</P>
</TEXT>
