<HEADLINE> Iran to Take Part in Earth Conference in New York </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Foreign Minister Ali Akbar
Velayati said here today that Iran will take part in the 19th
Earth Summit sponsored by the United Nations General Assembly due
to be held in New York on June 23-27.
</P>
<P>
Velayati himself will head a delegation there, the official
IRNA news agency said.
</P>
<P>
It is still not known if Velayati would take the advantage of
his visit to the U.S. to make any contacts with U.S. officials on
issues concerning the bilateral ties, which were severed 18 years
ago due to a hostage crisis.
</P>
<P>
The Earth Summit will study a universal action consistent
with the sustainable development. It will also adopt strategy to
prevent further deterioration of the environment and provide
fundamental methods of protecting environment in the 21st century.
</P>
</TEXT>
