<HEADLINE> S. Leone Fighting Kills 15 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FREETOWN, June 21 (Xinhua)-- At least 15 people including
eight Kamajors have died in the fierce fighting between the
traditional hunter militia and the Sierra Leone coupleader's
forces, military sources said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Three soldiers and four Kamajors were reportedly seriously
injured in the fighting which started Friday evening.
</P>
<P>
The government's reinforcement have been sent to southern S.
Leone's Gerihun area, to combat what a military official
described as "a showdown between the combatants."
</P>
<P>
The 1,000 strong Kamajors have set up a series of road blocks
along the Bo-Kenema highway and the Bo-Yele road to prevent troop
movement in the area which will encircle the Kamajors, a retired
military colonel said.
</P>
<P>
In another development, the secretary to the military, colonel
Tom Granby disclosed Saturday that Sierra Leone' s contigent in
west African peace keeping force (Ecomog) has been disarmed two
days ago by Ecomog commanders in Liberia.
</P>
<P>
The 300 man contigent was based at waterside on the Liberian
side of the border. "We see this as a ploy by Ecomog officials to
make the Sierra Leone open for the incursion into our country by
the mercenary group from Liberia with the assistance of Ecomog "
Gr Anby Granby said.
</P>
<P>
The military secretary called the action, "a dangerous
development" and called on ECOWAS heads of state "to intervene"
in this unprecedented action to disarm Sierra Leone soldiers who
are legally part of the peace keeping exercise in Liberia."
</P>
</TEXT>
