<HEADLINE> Jordanian Prime Minister Arrives in UAE </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Jordanian Prime Minister Abdul-
Salam Majali arrived here today for a three-day official visit
to the United Arab Emirates (UAE).
</P>
<P>
Majali is expected to discuss with UAE government officials
about stopping the implementation of a U.S. House of
Representatives resolution on recognizing Jerusalem as Israel's
undivided capital.
</P>
<P>
The UAE has criticized the U.S. resolution which was passed
last week and set aside 100 million U.S. dollars to move the
U.S. embassy from Tel Aviv to Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
Majali began his visit as Israeli troops and Palestinians
clashed in the West Bank cities of Hebron and Nablus. A week of
violence between the two sides reflect a further crack in the
stalled Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
The Middle East peace talks were set in deadlock after Israel
began the construction of a new settlement in East Jerusalem in
March. 
</P>
</TEXT>
