<HEADLINE> Photo Exhibition on Hong Kong Opens in Tanzania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
(By Pei Shanqin)
</P>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 21 (Xinhua) -- A photo exhibition entitled
"The Return of Hong Kong to the Motherland" opened at Tanzania
National Museum in the city this evening.
</P>
<P>
Opening the exhibition, the Tanzania Minister for Education
and Culture, Kapuya said, "we are here to celebrate the return of
Hong Kong to China which will officially take place on July 1,
1997."
</P>
<P>
"As we count down to that day we have every reason to be
happy. We are witnesses to the results of tough but sincere
negotiations between Chinese and British Governments which led to
the Sino-British Joint Declaration," he said.
</P>
<P>
The resuming of the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong by
China testifies the extent to which the motherland had a clear
understanding of her rights and the full respect she has for her
legal obligations, he said.
</P>
<P>
"We, Tanzanians, are inspired by the patience, understanding
and commitment shown by the government and people of the people's
Republic of China," Minister Kapuya said.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition, co-organized by the Chinese Embassy in
Tanzania and the Ministry for Education and Culture of Tanzania,
is composed of four parts - Hong Kong's history, its ties with
the inland areas, the process of transfer of power and today's
Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
About 150 people, including high-ranking government officials,
diplomatic envoys and representatives of the Chinese Embassy,
Chinese experts teams working in Tanzania as well as Chinese
companies based in Dar es Salaam, attended the opening ceremony,
which will last for 10 days. 
</P>
