that African countries should develop the African culture of
peace, tolerance and dialogue.
</P>
<P>
The African Day for Refugees was insituted in 1969 by the
Organization of African Unity to ensure the protection of
refugees on the continent. The day is observed each year on June
20.
</P>
<P>
This year's African Day for Refugees is celebrated under the theme:
Together in Search for Solution.
</P>
<P>
Following a recent census conducted by the UNHCR, Cameroun has
about 47,000 refugees. The total number of refugees in Africa
stands at six millions. 
</P>
