<HEADLINE> Dar es Salaam Harbour Dredging Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 21 (Xinhua) -- The dredging up of Dar es
Salaam harbour entrance project has already started, an official
of Tanzania Harbours Authority (THA) said today.
</P>
<P>
The Director General of the THA, Samson Luhigo told the
official Daily News here today that the project estimated to cost
23 million US Dollars will increase the port's handling capacity
of containers from 200 to 500 daily.
</P>
<P>
Luhigo said the process of dredging up the entrance will take
ten months. By September this year, the work will have gained
tempo, he added.
</P>
<P>
The director general said that upon completion of the work,
vessels of up to 40,000 tons can enter the harbour. At the
moment, only 25,000 tons vessels are allowed to sail through the
channel.
</P>
<P>
He said that widening of the entrance would eliminate the
problem of the tide which contributed immensely to THA's low
performance in handling containers.
</P>
<P>
At the moment, a vessel enters and leaves the port only when
the tide is favourable. A ship could finish off loading but some
times it would have to wait for favorable tide condition to get
out of the harbour, he said. Eenditem

