<DOCNO> XIE19970622.0038 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Christie Ends British Team Career with Winning Note </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Linford Christie, who competed for
the British team for the last time, ran a dead heat with Greece's
Georgios Panayiotopoulos in the 200 metes at the European Cup in
Munich on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Race judges ruled both runners had shared first place, allowing
Christie to end his last race for the British team on a winning
note.
</P>
<P>
Panayiotopoulos caught the 37-year-old Christie from behind and
race officials first ruled he broke the tape alone. But they
changed their decision to a dead heat after reviewing the replays.
</P>
<P>
The two runners were timed at 20.57 on a drizzly cold day, well
off the personal best of 20.09 that Christie ran in 1988.
</P>
<P>
Christie, the 1992 Olympic champion who plans to retire at the
end of the season, has been the dominant athlete at the event,
which brings together Europe's top eight track nations in team
competition.
</P>
<P>
With the dead heat win, and Saturday's triumph in the
100-meters, Christie finished unbeaten in 13 sprints over a decade
at the European Cup.
</P>
<P>
His two wins also helped Britain's men gain their first triumph
since 1989 at the European Cup after leading them to five straight
second-places.
</P>
<P>
Russia also handily beat Germany's women, the defending
champion. It recorded 127 points, while host Germany had 112.
</P>
<P>
Russia's Olga Kuzenkova also shattered the women's hammer throw
record by over three meters with a fling of 73.10, while Olympic
champion Vebjoern Rodal of Norway coasted to the 800 meters win as
expected.
</P>
<P>
Kuzenkova's fling easily broke the mark of 69.58 set earlier
this year by Romanian Melinte Mihaela, who threw 69.76 to finish
second.
</P>
<P>
Britain's Jonathan Edwards leaped to a year's best on his
second leap at 17.64 meters to win the triple jump.
</P>
<P>
Edwards, who owns the world record with a 1995 jump of 18.29,
had his best result in almost a year after three poor outings this
season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
