<HEADLINE> Thai Businessmen Plan to Invest in Jordan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, June 22 (Xinhua) -- A visiting businessmen delegation
from Thailand, Southeast Asia's main tourist destination,
today expressed the wishes to invest in Jordan's tourist sector.
</P>
<P>
Jordan's keenness to achieve a just and comprehensive peace in
the region encourages Thai businessmen to set up investment
projects in the kingdom, said head of the six-member delegation
Kim Watna, who is President of Thai Global, a holding company
with more than 20 firms specializing in tourism.
</P>
<P>
Thai businessmen plan to establish tourism facilities in
Jordan Valley and the Red Sea port city of Aqaba, said Watna
during his meeting with Prince Abdullah Hussein, the Regent.
</P>
<P>
The Regent underlined Jordan's readiness to provide facilities
and necessary services for Thai investors in the kingdom.
</P>
<P>
A statement from the Jordanian Ministry of Tourism and
Antiquities said that Thailand had expressed on several
occasions its interest in investing in Jordan's tourism sector.
</P>
<P>
The Thai delegation, which arrived here Saturday, is currently
touring Arab and European countries as well as the Palestinian
self-rule areas.
</P>
<P>
Tourism is one of Jordan's pillar industries. It reached heyday
in the 1980s and can earn some 600 million U.S. dollars a year,
one-tenth of its gross national product. 
</P>
