<HEADLINE> Jordanians Protest U.S. Decision on Jerusalem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Dozens of Jordanians held
demonstration here today before the U.S. Embassy to denounce a
U.S. Congress' decision to recognize Jerusalem as Israel's
"undivided" capital.
</P>
<P>
The Jordanian news Agency Petra reported that the protesters,
who were representatives from various non-governmental
organizations and groups, presented a condemnation note to the
embassy.
</P>
<P>
The demonstration, which lasted about an hour, went peacefully.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. House of Representatives approved on June 10 the
decision to recognize the holy city of Jerusalem as the undivided
capital of Israel and allocate 100 million U.S. dollars to remove
the U.S. embassy in Tel Aviv to the city. Many Arab countries have
voiced anger over the decision.
</P>
<P>
The sovereignty of Jerusalem has been a hot issue in the
Israeli-Palestinian peace negotiations as both sides claim the
city as their own state capital. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
