<HEADLINE> Colin McRae Retains Lead in China Rally 97 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 22 (Xinhua) -- British driver Colin McRae
retained his lead after two days of the three-day inaugural China
Rally 97 road race Sunday.
</P>
<P>
McRae, driving a Subaru, covered the eight special stages over
a distance of 143 kilometers in Huairou County in one hour 35
minutes 42 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Sweden's Kenneth Eriksson, also in a Subaru, held on to the
second place overall with one minute 37 seconds behind McRae. He
was followed by Japan's Yoshio Fujimoto in a Toyota, 9 minutes 31
seconds back.
</P>
<P>
Seventeen drivers are still in the rally from the 32 who set
out Saturday. The first day's stages, over a hilly course and in
scorching temperatures of 36 degrees saw 13 cars eliminated.
</P>
<P>
China Rally 97 features a total of 369 kilometers of special
stages. 
</P>
</TEXT>
