<HEADLINE> Adili Walked across Yangtze River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FENGJIE, CHONGQING, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Adili, a tightrope
walker from China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous region, materialised
his long-time dream after walking across the Yangtze River with
only 13.8 minutes here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Adili, the seventh generation of Dawazi family, walked on a
640.75-meter-long steel wire stretched 375 meters above the
Yangtze River to cross the Qutang Gorge, one of the well-known
Three Gorges on China's longest river.
</P>
<P>
The Uygur had long hoped to walk arcoss the Yangtze River, a
feat which had been achieved by Canadian tightrope walker Jay
Cochraine in 1995.
</P>
<P>
But the 51-year-old Cochrane, an America-based circus
performer, finished the walking in 53.2 minutes, more than 39
minutes than Adili's clocking. 
</P>
</TEXT>
