<HEADLINE> Kuzenkova Sets New Hammer World Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Olga Kuzenkova of Russia set a
women's world hammer record of 73.10 meters at the European Cup
Final in Munich, Germany, on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The previous mark of 69.58 meters was set by Mihaela Melinte of
Romania in Bucharest in March.
</P>
<P>
Kuzenkova reached 71.22 in her first throw and then improved it
to 73.10. Melinte also broke her own old record with a throw of
69.76. 
</P>
