<HEADLINE> Chernomyrdin Confident in Russia-China Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Russian Prime Minister Viktor
Chernomyrdin, who will leave for China on June 26 for a three-day
official visit, said here today that the main purpose of his visit
to China is "to continue the development of cooperation between
the two countries."
</P>
<P>
Chernomyrdin made the remarks in an interview with Xinhua after
laying a wreath on the Tomb of Unknown Soldiers near the Red
Square on the occasion of the 56th anniversary of the Patriotic
War taken by the former Soviet Union.
</P>
<P>
He said, "as you know, we (Russia and China) made some plans
when Chinese Premier Li Peng came to Moscow in December last year,
and now I fly to Beijing" to fix these plans.
</P>
<P>
Asked about the prospects of the China-Russia relations,
Chernomyrdin said, "I can say that the prospects of the relations
between the two countries are good, and the areas of cooperation
are broad."
</P>
<P>
He disclosed that the Russian government delegation will
discuss and solve many important issues in Beijing, mainly the
issues concerning economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He said, "there are tremendous potentialities and many
opportunities we should use for developing the economic
cooperation between Russia and China."
</P>
<P>
"At present, both countries have a desire for cooperation,
which is very possible. So, I am in a good mood to visit China,"
Chernomyrdin added. 
</P>
