<HEADLINE> India to Manufacture Air Defense Ship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 22 (Xinhua) -- India is planning to manufacture
its own air defense ship (ADS), a smaller version of an aircraft
carrier, defense sources said here today.
</P>
<P>
The move is in line with India's policy of achieving maximum
localization and enhancing self-reliance in a phased manner.
</P>
<P>
India's first aircraft carrier, INS Vikrant, was decommissioned
earlier this year. The other aircraft carrier, INS Viraat, would
also be non-operational for a certain period once the proposal for
its modernization is sanctioned.
</P>
<P>
India has decided against going in for the Russian aircraft
carrier, Gorshkov, as it was not being offered at a price which
could suit the country's budget, the same sources said.
</P>
<P>
A defense ship, which is much cheaper than an aircraft carrier,
is a faster and agile vessel suitable for operational needs in the
region, the sources added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
