"a reaffirmation of the democratic process" and hoped that
"estrangements" between the people of Iran and the United
States could be "bridged".
</P>
<P>
On May 27, Iranian President-elect Mohammad Khatami called
the United States to abandon its hostile policy toward the
Islamic Republic, saying "as long as the U.S. is after harming
Iran's interests and independence, Iran will have no relations
with the U.S.."
</P>
<P>
"Iran will not tolerate any domination-seeking power. Any
change in our relations with the United States depends on
change in attitude of the U.S.," said the 54-year-old new
president.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. severed diplomatic relations with Iran in 1979 after
Iranian Islamic militants occupied the U.S. embassy in Tehran and
took 52 diplomats and employees as hostages. The U.S. has been
keeping economic sanctions against Iran ever since.
</P>
<P>
The Earth Summit scheduled to open Monday is to be attended by
70 leaders and is a follow-up to the Earth Summit Conference
held in Rio De Janeiro in 1992. 
</P>
