<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Northeast China Encouraging Inventions, Updating Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Northeast China's Liaoning
Province has started a campaign to encourage local state-owned
enterprises to invent more and to improve technology.
</P>
<P>
"The purpose is to improve the quality of industrial goods made
in Liaoning, and to better the performance of these enterprises,"
local officials say.
</P>
<P>
Liaoning is one of China's key industrial bases, boasting one
tenth of the country's large and medium-sized enterprises. But
most of these state-owned enterprises have been losing money since
the country started a reform to develop a market economy.
</P>
<P>
"The equipment is deteriorating in these enterprises, and the
technology content of their products is poor," officials say. So,
according to the government, each local enterprise has to bring at
least one new product into production by the end of the century.
</P>
<P>
The enterprises are also encouraged to increase cooperation
with universities and colleges.
</P>
<P>
About 4,500 new products are expected to be put into production
in this year, and the province's new industrial product value will
reach 25 billion yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
