<HEADLINE> Foreign Exchange Reserves Increase in Tanzania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Gross foreign exchange
reserves of the Bank of Tanzania (BoT) increased from 240.2
million US Dollars in June 1996 to 390.2 miillion US Dollars by
the end of April, 1997, local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
The reserves were sufficient to cover over three months of the
country's imports requirements, the BoT said in its monetary
policy statement for 1997/98 financial year which was presented
to the National Assembly Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
