<HEADLINE> Moi Ready to Discuss Political Reforms with </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan President Daniel arap Moi
will soon meet newly-installed Catholic primate Ndingi Mwana'a
Nzeki to discuss political reforms, The Sunday Nation reported
today.
</P>
<P>
The Kenyan leader made the statement on Saturday during the
official enthronement of the Most Reverent Nzeki as the head of
the Catholic Church in Kenya.
</P>
<P>
Many lives had been lost in Africa due to civil strife or
wars, said Moi, adding that he would not like to see the same
happen in Kenya.
</P>
<P>
His only concern is to ensure that his country avoid
bloodshed and destruction in some African countries resulted from
civil strife, he said.
</P>
<P>
On the same occasion, church leaders attending the ceremony
condemned acts of violence and lawlessness taken place recently
in the East African country.
</P>
<P>
They urged both the government and opposition leaders to
resort to dialogue to seek for a lasting solution to the current
stand-off over constitutional reforms.
</P>
<P>
Reverent John Njue, the Chairman of the Kenya Episcopal
Conference, stated that the church condemned all forms of
violence as recently witnessed in the country, adding that war
would not solve Kenya's problems. 
</P>
</TEXT>
