<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Xinhua Article to Mark 10-Day Countdown of HK's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 22 (Xinhua) -- The Xinhua Daily Telegram today
frontpaged an article, written on Saturday to mark the 10-day
countdown of the return of Hong Kong to the motherland on July 1.
</P>
<P>
The article, titled "Great Changes, and Reflections on
History", reviewed the aggressions old China had suffered from
in the past century and the numerous campaigns launched by the
Chinese people to fight against foreign invaders.
</P>
<P>
Places such as the Chung Ying Street at the boundary between
Guangdong and Hong Kong, the Yuanmingyuan Park in Beijing, the
Wusongkou Port in Shanghai, and the Dagukou Port in Tianjin had
witnessed the foreign aggressions more than 100 years ago, the
article said, adding that they have benefited from the great
changes taken place since the founding of new China in 1949,
especially from the reform and open-up policies.
</P>
<P>
The past history demonstrated that implementing Deng Xiaoping's
theory on building socialism with Chinese characteristics is the
only way that helps China grow strong and win respect in the
world, the article concluded.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
