<HEADLINE> Shanghai Hosts International Gymnastics Invitational </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai will play hosts to the
China-Cup International Gymnastics Invitational as a warm-up for
the World Gymnastics Championships in August.
</P>
<P>
The invitational tournament, slated from June 24 to 26, will
feature the Olympians from Belarus, Ukraine, Romania and the
first-string members of the Chinese national squad.
</P>
<P>
Among the top-notched gymnasts include Elena Piskoun of
Belarus, winner of the uneven bar in the 1996 World Championships,
Alexandra Marinescu of Romania, member of the champions team in
the 1995 World Championships, and her teammates Mirela Tugurlan,
member of Atlanta third-place team.
</P>
<P>
Romania also dispatched its top men gymnasts of Andrian
Lanculescu and Nistor Sandro, both were members of the third place
team in the 1995 World Championships.
</P>
<P>
The Ukrainian squad was spearheaded by Vladimir Shamenko and
Yuri Yermakov, both were members of the team that finished third
in the 1996 Atlanta Olympics.
</P>
<P>
The host will feature eight Olympians, including six world
champions, for the tournament. They are men gymnasts Zhang
Jinjing, Shen Jian, Fan Bin and Fan Hongbin, as the women squad
will be composed of Mo Huilan, Kui Yuanyuan, Ji Liya and Mei Fei.
</P>
<P>
A total of 14 gold titles will be contested in the three-day
event with a prize money of 200,000 Renminbi (25,000 US dollars)
at stake.
</P>
<P>
The China-Cup invitational had been held annually after its
inuguration in 1988. 
</P>
</TEXT>
