<HEADLINE> Rebels Attack Western Uganda Towns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Rebels of the Allied Democratic
Forces (ADF) harassed towns of Kaserse and Bundibugyo in western
Uganda for the past two days, and were repulsed by the government
troops, local media reported today.
</P>
<P>
On Friday, some 30 rebels raided a police post in Kaserse and
killed five civilians before fleeing the town when a government
unit launched a counter attack.
</P>
<P>
At the same day in Bundibugyo, 17 rebels penetrated the
defense line of the town and attacked at midnight. They fled to a
valley eight kilometers from the town when the government troops
reacted. The clashes lasted until Saturday morning.
</P>
<P>
The raids in Bndibugyo and Kasese are the second within a
week.
</P>
<P>
ADF is a rebel group active in western Uganda. An earlier
official estimate put their number at 400 to 500. 
</P>
</TEXT>
