<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-22 08:16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Lebanon Calls on Israel to Implement UN Resolution </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Lebanese Foreign Minister Farez
Boueiz today urged Israel to implement U.N. resolution 425 to
withdraw from south Lebanon unconditionally.
</P>
<P>
The minister made the call in an interview with the Paris-based
Orient Radio which quoted him as calling on France to ask Israel
to clarify its position on the U.N. Security Council Resolution
425.
</P>
<P>
Boueiz said that Israel knows exactly that only through the
implementation of Resolution 425, which demands an unconditional
Israeli withdrawal from south Lebanon, the violence in south
Lebanon can be stopped.
</P>
<P>
The Lebanese foreign minister made the statement in response
to Israeli Defense Minister Yitzhak Mordechai's announcement
Friday that he had asked France to use its influence on the
Lebanese government and the army to fight terrorism and search
for ways to reduce violence and find solutions to the Lebanese
dilemma.
</P>
<P>
"I think the French should put a clear question upon the
Israelis about their position on the implementation of Resolution
425 and their position on the peace process, and the French
should not accept new suggestions which could push the peace
process backward," Boueiz said to the radio.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the land-for-peace principle, Boueiz said: "The
Israeli government also knows that the Madrid mechanism as it
was decided and agreed upon is a guarantee to lead all the
parties involved to a comprehensive and lasting peace."
</P>
<P>
"Those who refuse to implement Resolution 425, and those who
damage the peace process by all means are not qualified to ask
why the violence has prevailed and why the peace has not been
established," Boueiz noted.  
</P>
</TEXT>
