<HEADLINE> Brewer Takes Vacant IBF Super Middlweight Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 21 (Xinhua) -- American Charles Brewer stopped
South African Gary Ballard in the fifth round in Florida on
Saturday to take the vacant International Boxing Federation super
middlweight title.
</P>
<P>
Brewer, 27, took his record to 29-5, with 20 victories inside
the distance, while Ballard fell to 22-3 with one draw.
</P>
<P>
Francois Botha of South Africa turned in another lackluster
performance with a 12-round unanimous decision against American
journeyman Lee Gilbert.
</P>
<P>
Gilbert, 31, came into the bout undefeated against no-name
opposition. He kept the fight close, but Botha sealed the decision
with a knockdown in the 11th round.
</P>
<P>
Botha improved his record to 37-1 with 21 knockouts while
Gilbert fell to 17-1.
</P>
<P>
The card produced two more new world champions. Jamaican Uriah
Grant upset American Adolpho Washington with a majority decision
to claim Washington's IBF cruiserweight title.
</P>
<P>
And Ghana's Nana Konadu reclaimed the World Boxing Association
bantamweight title by stopping Thailand's Daorung Siriwat in the
seventh round.
</P>
<P>
Konadu, who lost the title eight months ago, regained it when
the referee stopped the fight at 2:20 of the seventh. 
</P>
</TEXT>
