<HEADLINE> Argentina Beaten by Peru in Copa America </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Argentina suffered a 2-1
defeat against Peru as three of its players were sent off in the
quarterfinal of the Copa America tournament on Sucre, Bolivia on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Two were dismissed in a fight when Marcelo Gallardo rushed to
catch the ball after converting a penalty for Argentina to make
the score 2-1.
</P>
<P>
Peru goalkeeper Miguel Miranda got to the ball at the same time
as Gallardo and the two began fighting for the ball, leading to a
brawl involving most of the players on the field.
</P>
<P>
Gallardo and Eduardo Berizzo were shown the red card. Gustavo
Zapata was later sent off for a second offence.
</P>
<P>
Eddie Carazas and Martin Hidalgo had earlier put Peru 2-0
ahead, setting them up for a deserved victory in which goalkeeper
Miguel Miranda performed heroics.
</P>
<P>
Both teams had brought second-string outfits to the tournament,
preferring to rest their top players for the World Cup qualifying
matches. 
</P>
