<HEADLINE> Vice Chairman of Former Romanian Ruling Party Quits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Teodor Melescanu, vice chairman
of the former ruling Romanian Social Democratic Party, and four
other senior party officials have quited the party.
</P>
<P>
At the national party congress held on Friday and Saturday,
Melescanu left the party after an unsuccessful attempt to purge
party leaders charged with corruption, saying the party was
"stamped with the brand of corruption."
</P>
<P>
However, Party Chairman Ion Illiescu, the former Romanian
president, said Melescanu's remarks represent "the interest of
small cliques," while Party First Vice Chairman Adrian Nastase
accused Melescanu of attempting to seize the party's second
position.
</P>
<P>
