<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sinopec to Invest in Renovation Instead of Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 22 (Xinhua) -- China Petrochemical Corp (Sinopec)
will upgrade its existing enterprises rather than launch new
projects in the Ninth Five-Year Plan (1996-2000), today's China
Daily reported.
</P>
<P>
Sinopec President Sheng Huaren said the plan fit the national
strategy to shift into an intensive economic growth mode.
</P>
<P>
Sinopec has carried out largescale infrastructure construction
since its establishment in 1983. It has five ethylene lines each
capable of producing 300,000 tons and six large fertilizer
production lines. It also has increased refining capacity.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the company processed 118 million tons of crude oil,
48 million tons more than its 1983 processing capacity.
</P>
<P>
It produced 2.45 million tons of ethylene in 1996, compared to
500,000 tons in 1983.
</P>
<P>
The company is expected to spend half its fixed investment on
technical innovations in the next three years, Sheng said.
</P>
<P>
He said the company is ready to increase the capacity of its
ethylene production lines to 600,000 tons each from 300,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
The company would not establish new refinery enterprises in the
next three years. Instead, it is expected to reconstruct current
enterprises to improve quality and increase quantity, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said the company is expected to reduce about one-third of
its staff to improve efficiency. Jobs will be created by new
businesses from other industries to employ the laid-off people.
</P>
<P>
Sinopec currently employs 650,000 people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
