<HEADLINE> Foot-and-Mouth Disease Eradication Sought in S.A. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Delegations from
Bolivia, Colombia, Ecuador, Peru, and Venezuela will start a
meeting in this city next Monday to plan the eradication of
foot-and-mouth disease.
</P>
<P>
The delegations will report on the programs implemented in
their countries in curing the cattle sickness and guidelines to
follow in the next months, according to the Colombian Agriculture
Ministry today.
</P>
<P>
The foot-and-mouth fever that has affected cattles in the
region since 1950 limits the possibilities of the Andean producers
to enter the international market with beef and its by-products.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will paralle the Agroexpo-97, an agriculture and
livestock fair in Colombia considered one of the most important
events in Latin America. 
</P>
