<HEADLINE> Novotna Faces Sanchez Vicario in Eastbourne Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Arantxa Sanchez Vicario battled
through the quarter and semi finals on Saturday, begging mercy for
a delay of the final against Jana Novotna.
</P>
<P>
As matches were delayed two days by rain, organisers hoped to
cram in the final three rounds of the Eastbourne tournament on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Sanchez Vicario was exhausted after playing two hard matches on
Saturday. The Spaniard beat Irina Spirlea in the quarter-finals
and Brenda Schultz-McCarthy in the second semifinal on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
She asked not to be sent straight back on court and to her
wishes, Novotna agreed.
</P>
<P>
The final will be played at 1000 GMT (1100 local) on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Novotna, who beat Natasha Zvereva 6-7, 6-0, 7-5 in the earlier
semifinal, had at least had an hour's rest while Sanchez Vicario
beat Schultz-McCarthy 7-5, 6-1.
</P>
<P>
Early on Saturday, Schultz-McCarthy, the eighth seed, defeated
defending champion Monica Seles 7-5, 7-5 in a quarter-final which
began on Thursday and was postponed because of the rain.
</P>
<P>
On Saturday, second seed Novotna first resumed her
quarter-final against Japan's Ai Sugiyama which was interrupted by
rain on Friday with the Czech 6-2, 6-5 up and the score at 15-15.
</P>
<P>
As Novotna was three more points away from the victory, she
took the hard route, failing to convert a matchpoint and then
hitting a double fault to surrender a break which took the second
set to the tiebreak which Sugiyama won 8-6.
</P>
<P>
In the third set, Novotna played perfect serve-and-volley one
minute but hit errors the next before a break of serve in the 10th
game finally gave her victory.
</P>
<P>
In the semifinal against Belarussian Zvereva, Novotna
surrendered a 5-3 lead in the opening set before Zvereva won the
tiebreak 9-7.
</P>
<P>
Zvereva went down to love in a second set which saw one game go
11 times to deuce before Novotna converted her eighth breakpoint
and saved four more matchpoints in the third set before Novotna
won 7-5.
</P>
<P>
Zvereva had beaten Frenchwoman Nathalie Tauziat 6-4 5-7 6-4 in
the quarter-finals. Tauziat later withdrew from a doubles match
with a pulled thigh muscle. 
</P>
</TEXT>
