<HEADLINE> Overseas Investment Increasing in Northeast China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Dalian, an open coastal city in
northeast China's Liaoning Province, has become a favorite
investment spot for overseas business people.
</P>
<P>
The city has now attracted large sums of overseas investment
from 59 countries and regions since it first opened to the outside
world in 1984.
</P>
<P>
Dalian has so far set up 4,124 Sino-foreign joint ventures,
with pledged overseas financing reaching 6.1 billion US dollars,
and 965 foreign-owned businesses, with contracted overseas funding
reaching nearly 3.4 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the city also has 915 Sino-foreign cooperative
firms, which use more than 1.2 billion US dollars in contracted
overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
Dalian currently has 15 foreign-funded enterprises with
investment surpassing 100 million US dollars each.
</P>
<P>
And 700 local foreign-funded enterprises have so far increased
investment in the city by as much as 2.1 billion US
dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
