<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Private Firms Eligible For Listing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 22 (Xinhua) -- The central government is for the
first time offering private firms a niche in the stock market,
according to the "Business Weekly".
</P>
<P>
Duojia Co., a Hubei-based textile manufacturer, is the first to
benefit from the decision. It was listed on the Shanghai Stock
Exchange on June 6.
</P>
<P>
The second, Sichuan agricultural company Hejia, will make its
debut on Thursday in the same market.
</P>
<P>
Although a few non-State firms were already listed under the
recommendation of provincial governments before the two's listing,
the market has been generally considered a funding source
primarily for the State sector, the paper says.
</P>
<P>
The country's provinces and industry ministries share listing
companies assigned by the government every year. The All-China
Federation of Industry and Commerce (ACFIC), China's
private-sector chamber of commerce, has just began to recommend
private firms using quotas from the central government.
</P>
<P>
Duojia and Hejia's listing are expected to positively affect
China's 800,000 private firms, encouraging them to upgrade, said
Ouyang Xiaoming, an official with ACFIC.
</P>
<P>
Mushrooming private firms were one of the most obvious direct
results of China's economic reforms in the early 1980s.
</P>
<P>
The sector has become a significant part of the country's
economy. Some elite companies have emerged with more than one
billion yuan in assets each. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970622.0170 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Accord Guaranteeing Albanian Elections to be Signed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Leaders of the Albanian coalition
parties will meet here on Monday to sign an accord for
guaranteeing the June 29 elections, organizers of the meeting
announced today.
</P>
<P>
Participants at the meeting will be Tritan Sheu, chairman of
President Sali Berisha's Democratic Party, Fatos Nano of the
Socialist Party and leaders of the opposition to the president.
</P>
<P>
No contents of the accord have been released, but the
Community of Saint Egidio, a Catholic organization, said the
accord is to "reduce mutual concerns and outline a framework for
political debate and cooperation for the final stages of the
electoral campaign and the beginning of a new democratic era in
Albania." 
</P>
</TEXT>
