<HEADLINE> Brief Latin American Cultural News </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, June 21 (Xinhua) -- The following are news about
culture, arts, and entertainment related events occurred in the
last few days in Latin American countries:

Argentine Dancer Julio Bocca Gets Award in New York
</P>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES -- Argentine dancer Julio Bocca received this week
in New York the King David Prize, awarded by the Argentine House
in Israel Holy Land, and the Howard Gilman Foundation, for the
excellence of his work and his continued dedication to make known
the Argentine artistic values and culture.
</P>
<P>
Bocca, first dancer of the American Ballet Theater of the
United States, is one of the most important dancer at an
international level.
</P>
<P>
The Argentine House in Israel Holy Land is an ecumenical
organization founded in 1966 by Argentine writer Jorge Luis Borges
and his countryman, painter Raul Soldi. Its main purpose is to
stimulate cultural interactions.

Israeli Cinema Week Being Held in Montevideo
</P>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO -- The Israeli Cinema Week is being held June 21 to
28 in Uruguay with the screening of seven films, six of them made
in the eighties.
</P>
<P>
The other film, "Rosa Te Amo" won the Oscar to the best foreign
film in 1971.
</P>
<P>
According to the organizers, this picture, of great thematic
and stylistic variet, shows the complexities of the contemporary
reality and of the very conflictive political and social
circumstance of Israel.

Chinese Quartet With Piano Visits Colombia
</P>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA -- The Quartet With Piano of Beijing arrived
to Colombia to perform in several cities invited by the Antonio
Narino University.
</P>
<P>
The young Chinese musicians quartet will play in Barranquilla,
Medellin, Armenia, Popayan and Santafe de Bogota, the capital of
the country.
</P>
<P>
The musicians played works of Schumann, Mozart, and Telemann.

UNESCO Awards "Camera 1997" Prize to Mexican TV Channel 22
</P>
<P>
MEXICO CITY -- The Mexican television Channel 22 will be
awarded in a near future with the "Camera 1997" Prize, given every
year by the United Nations Education, Science, and Culture
Organization (UNESCO).
</P>
<P>
The reason of awarding Channel 22 of Mexico the prize is for
spreading and promoting new projects of national character related
to the cultural manifestations of Mexican culture.
</P>
<P>
Other organizations to be awarded are the Museum of Mankind of
London, and the "Decouvertes" publications collection of the
Gallimard editorial house of France. enditem


nnnn
</P>
